title: Afghan Uyghurs Fear Deportation as Taliban Cozy Up to China
content: Members of the ethnic group, seen by China as potential extremists, are afraid they will be sent there as part of a deal for economic aid.

title: Europe Tightens Purse Strings to Try to Pressure Poland and Hungary
content: Frustrations over rule of law violations in the two countries have prompted the European Union to block payments in an effort to bolster legal action.

title: Catalan Separatist Leader, Carles Puigdemont, Is Arrested in Italy
content: The arrest of Mr. Puigdemont, on the island of Sardinia, came on a warrant issued by Spain’s Supreme Court on charges of sedition.

title: New Taliban Guidelines Stir Fear About the Future of Press Freedom
content: The directives for journalists include rules against publishing topics in conflict with Islam or insulting to national personalities.

title: Thousands of Boko Haram Members Surrendered. They Moved In Next Door.
content: Fighters and family members of a terrorist group in Nigeria have defected in droves since the death of their leader. They’ve been relocated to a city they once terrorized.

title: Boris Johnson Cuts a Colorful Swath in U.S., but to What End?
content: U.K.’s prime minister makes headlines, yet experts say it is unclear if his lighthearted style is helping stake out a post-Brexit role on the global stage.

title: Has Covid Cost Australia Its Love for Freedom?
content: Half the country is locked down, and its borders remain closed. But most Australians are willing to make these sacrifices in pursuit of a collective freedom from fear of the virus.

title: A senior U.S. diplomat to Haiti resigns, citing the Biden administration’s ‘inhumane’ deportation policy.
content: The diplomat, Daniel Foote, was appointed special envoy to Haiti in July, just weeks after President Jovenel Moïse was assassinated.

title: Australia Court Orders Ex-Principal to Be Tried on Abuse Charges
content: Malka Leifer, who was extradited from Israel after a long battle, pleaded not guilty to 70 counts.

title: Hong Kong Is Holding Elections. It Wants Them to Look Real.
content: China has already determined the outcome, but the government is pressuring opposition parties to participate to lend the vote legitimacy.

title: C.D.C. Chief Overrules Agency Panel and Recommends Pfizer-BioNTech Boosters for Workers at Risk
content: In a highly unusual decision, the C.D.C. director, Rochelle Walensky, reversed a move by agency advisers and endorsed additional doses of the Pfizer-BioNTech vaccine for health care workers, teachers and other workers at risk.

title: The Future Is Knocking on Australia’s Door
content: With Covid, global security and climate change, the status quo has started to shift.

title: Your Friday Briefing
content: Booster shots in the U.S.

title: In Biden’s Foreign Policy, Friends and Foes Claim Echoes of Trump
content: President Biden’s speech at the U.N. was a stark contrast to President Donald J. Trump’s. But it came amid complaints that some of Mr. Biden’s policy moves echoed his predecessor’s approach.

title: Secret Hearing Focuses on Hidden Microphones at Guantánamo Prison
content: Hearings resumed in the destroyer Cole bombing case after a 600-day delay caused by the pandemic.

title: Gira Sarabhai, Designer Who Helped Shape Modern India, Dies at 97
content: The youngest daughter of an influential family of industrialists, she trained with Frank Lloyd Wright before returning to India and founding design institutions.

title: Your Friday Briefing
content: The U.S. prepares for vaccine boosters.

title: Cuba expects to reach ‘full immunization’ with homegrown vaccines by Dec. 31.
content: The vaccines developed in Cuba, which have yet to receive W.H.O. approval, are being administered to adults and children as young as 2.

title: House approves $1 billion for the Iron Dome as Democrats feud over Israel.
content: Progressives balked at sending military aid to a country they accuse of human rights abuses, angering centrists and Jewish lawmakers who said the United States must support a crucial ally.

title: Navalny to the Russian Opposition: ‘Be Discouraged, a Little Bit’
content: Emblematic of the beleaguered state of the opposition, a forlorn group of volunteers maintains a 24-hour vigil at the spot where a prominent democracy advocate was killed in 2015.

title: Tropical Storm Sam Is Expected to Become Major Hurricane by the Weekend
content: Sam, the fourth named storm to form in less than a week, is in the Atlantic was expected to strengthen into a “major” hurricane by the weekend.

title: International Battle Over 6-Year-Old Cable-Car Survivor Goes to Court
content: The fate of Eitan Biran, whose parents were killed at an Italian mountain resort in May, has become an international cause pitting relatives in Israel against those in Italy.

title: An Uncomfortable Question in France: Are We Still a Great Power?
content: The failed submarine deal with Australia raises questions about whether there is an unbridgeable divide between France’s vision of itself on the world stage and its actual power.

title: African health experts hail Biden’s vaccine pledge, but call for more transparency.
content: The continent, which has the lowest Covid-19 vaccination rate, has suffered not only from a shortage of vaccines but also from delayed and inconsistent deliveries of doses.

title: Congressional Brinkmanship
content: Is the U.S. government headed for another showdown over the debt ceiling?

title: New Zealand wants vaccination rates near 90 percent.
content: The government is reviewing a new study, which has yet to be peer-reviewed, that shows that lockdowns would not be necessary once vaccination levels reached 90 percent.

title: In Sicily Slums, a 113-Year Wait for Housing May Be Over
content: After a 1908 earthquake in Messina, the displaced were moved into temporary shacks. Thousands still live in squalor, but the pandemic has pushed Rome to take action at last.

title: Your Thursday Briefing
content: Biden’s call for global vaccine cooperation.

title: Days Before Germans Vote, Merkel Is Where She Didn’t Want to Be: On the Stump
content: The race for chancellor is tightening, but Angela Merkel says Armin Laschet is the man to fill her shoes.

title: At Covid Summit, Biden Sets Ambitious Goals for Vaccinating the World
content: But his plans face a tough road as pressure grows for big pharmaceutical companies to share their vaccine technologies with poorer nations.
